152	2698	16	b. Scraping tools used to remove blistered paint must be kept sharp to be effective .
153	2714	24	Do all scraping in the direction of the wood grain to prevent shredding of wood fibers and gouging of the bare wood surface .
154	2738	14	This phase of paint removal is important in preparing the surface for sanding .
155	2752	15	c. All areas stripped as previously described are now ready for sanding before priming .
156	2767	21	Hand sanding , with wooden blocks where practicable , using the correct grit paper , is the prescribed final step .
157	2788	22	Careful dusting before paint application is absolutely necessary to achieve a good primer bond , or bond between subsequent paint coats .
158	2810	15	( 1 ) Power disc sanders are not authorized for use in surface preparation .
159	2825	16	Improper use of the disc sander is the biggest cause of uneven surfaces and damage .
160	2841	24	( 2 ) Belt sanders and vibrating sanders are authorized for use in preparing the hull freeboard for priming and top - coating .
